@Marvel Entertainment¬†@Marvel Movies¬†I think if you and @Universal Studios Hollywood¬†can work out an agreement to do an Incredible Hulk 2, you should treat the series like the "Wrestler format." Godzilla is a great example of this format, where the movie's main attraction is the monster's fighting. That seems to be the best way to portray the Hulk. Remember, it's not so much about suppressing the hulk anymore, as Bruce has somewhat learned to control him for the most part for the better.¬†

We know Samuel Sterns has become the Leader and is now locked up with SHIELD. Have Bruce be studying him, trying to maybe repay him as part of a neat emotional subplot, and he decides to try and make Hulk his weapon. When this attempt fails, he creates a monster that can defeat the Hulk, say kidnapping General Ross and making him Red Hulk or any other assortment of monsters in the Hulk comics.
